author: @anaikapaul7707
text: It's really fun and enriching to see how each member of BTS has a simple and really refreshing personality.  I always enjoy watching them talk to each other or with other people and I'm not going to lie I've learned a lot from them. It may seem strange but I have progressed in human relationships thanks to them, I tell the people around me that I love them more often, I listen to people more, I help them, I support them if necessary and all that is the influence that BTS has on me. Of course I did not stan them very early because I did not know their existence but I met them when I was at the lowest point of my life even if this life still has not improved but still BTS brings me the smile, the comfort and the joy that I deserve. I never had favorite artists before them they are the only ones and I do not regret it. I only hope that they know that their entire existence makes me happy but not only me I think other fans think the same way as me. I hope one day I will see you in concert even if it is a totally impossible dream for me but I keep believing in it because I never know what the future holds for me.  As Suga said in one of his songs: " Future's gonna be okay" .

author: @Layla-jf7zo
text:
Mi Querido Yoongi:
Ya no sientas vergüenza. Ya no te disculpes más. Es suficiente.
Quienes te hemos apoyado y amado con sinceridad lo seguiremos haciendo. Tus "malas acciones" como las llamas fueron un error. Un error que cometiste porque eres humano, al igual que todos nosotros. Esta falta no borra el amor que sentimos por ti, ni el amor que nos has dado a lo largo de los años a través de tus actos, tus palabras y tus canciones.

Reconocer tu error y aceptarlo es un acto de valentía y madurez. Aún en estas circunstancias sigues siendo una fuente de inspiración, sabes por qué? Porque tú aceptas la responsabilidad de tus actos y no huyes de ella, mientras que no todas las personas en este mundo son capaces de aceptar sus errores y enmendarlos. Tú sí. Y eso tiene un valor muy significativo, como persona y como figura pública. 

Escribiste ese mensaje para que seamos los primeros en saberlo. Pensar que, aún mientras atravesabas esos duros momentos pensabas en nosotros, demuestra lo mucho que significamos para ti. Quizá en ese momento hubo prisa, pero tu explicación fue sincera y dijiste la verdad desde el principio. Para nosotros, saber que estabas bien, que no te habías hecho daño y que no había terceros afectados calmó nuestro corazón. Gracias por habérnoslo dicho. 

Si cariño, esto servirá como un aprendizaje, sin que ello signifique que debas vivir con remordimiento hasta el final. No es necesario atormentarse. No nos has lastimado, no hay heridas que curar. Los bellos recuerdos que hemos creado siguen intactos y así seguirán siempre. El vínculo que nos une es sincero y leal y no va a cambiar. Quienes te hemos apoyado y aplaudido lo seguiremos haciendo porque te amamos. Eres una parte significativa de nuestras vidas. 

Me motivaste a seguir adelante. Me diste fuerza en tiempos difíciles. Agradezco a Dios por el día en que tú y los chicos llegaron a mi vida. Hoy que me necesitas quiero ser yo quien te apoye, quien te de palabras de aliento, quien te diga lo valioso que eres y lo mucho que significas para mí. Siempre puedes contar con mi amor. Te amo mucho, te amo de corazón!

흑 보고싶다 얘들아ㅠㅠ 보고싶어서 또 왔어.. 너희들의 음악으로 인생을 변화 시켜나가는 1인 여기 또 있어..
복수만 꿈꾸며 사느라 그 분노가 내 자신을 집어삼키는걸 모르고 있었는데 너희들의 음악으로 가사로 메세지로 치유해 나가며 이 전과는 전혀 다른 삶을 꿈꾸게 되었다. 왜 이제서야 너희들을 알게 됐을까, 좀 더 빨랐다면 나도 너희들을 지키고 너희의 음악으로 지옥 같았던 그 순간을 버텨내고 있던 나를 지킬 수 있지 않을까 싶지만... 이미 지나가 버린 일.. 지금이라도 열심히 살려고. 일단 목표는 나도 25년까지 뭔가 가시적인 성과를 내는거야. 너희들이 복귀하는 그날까지 누나도 열심히 살고 있을게. 고마워 방탄해줘서 영광이고 그저 감사해 사랑해 보라해.

author: @7daifan
text: Every time I see the two of them talking I can't help but think how eloquently they speak. It's no wonder that they're responsible for writing a majority of lyrics in a majority of the group's songs. Every member of BTS brings something special to the group, all of them have unique talents, but it was these two that kind of started it all, it's like watching parents talk about their family, about their baby. I feel so much wisdom in their words, and I am so proud of who they were, who they are, and who they are becoming. When I listen to Namjoon or Yoongi speak, I almost always leave with something new to think about that will help better my own life. They never have to worry about ARMY leaving. I know I will always stay by their side. I may not be able to watch all the content, or buy all the merch, but I will always be here, so long as they need me.  I truly believe only ARMY can understand just what I mean when I say that, I Love Them. always.

It is the wish of an Indian Army.

author: @lov3ly_tear
text:
32:52 wow...esta parte de la entrevista me golpeó, tanto que tuve que pausar el video por un momento. Arrepentimiento y culpa del pasado, preocupación y miedo por el futuro, nunca se me había pasado por la cabeza algo como "mi sueño es vivir en el presente" ahora que se me presenta esa idea suena muy difícil de hacer, no tengo un sueño definido pero quiero tener uno, a pesar de no tener un sueño claro solo sé que quiero ser feliz y siempre he pensado en la felicidad como algo del futuro...tal vez debería concentrarme en el presente. Vivir en el presente es algo extremadamente difícil para mí pero quiero lograrlo, quiero deshacerme que las cadenas llamadas "pasado y futuro" que me arrastran constantemente.
Puede que no lo parezca pero acabo de tener una crisis existencial gracias a una frase que dijo un tipo famoso que ni siquiera sabe de mi existencia XD estoy pasando por un momento difícil, aunque él no lo sepa en serio me ayudó mucho, muchas gracias Nam💙

author: @김세렌-613
text: 25:22 음악의 원동력이 뭐냐는 남준이의 질문에 0.1초도 생각하지 않고 아미들을 위해 음악을 계속 한다고 답한 슈가와 슈가의 답을 듣고 더 멋진 명언을 남긴 남준이까지. 솔직히 많은 사람들이 방탄소년단을 욕하고 까내리려고 수단과 방법을 가리지 않는 모습은 아미로써 매우 화나고 짜증나는 일이지만 그 사람들을 상대하면, 관심을 주면 더 그럴 것을 알기 때문에 아미들은 그저 방탄소년단을 더 사랑하고 믿고 방탄소년단의 음악을 듣고 살아가는 것이 제일이라고 본다. 우리를 위해 음악을 하고 많은 욕들을 감수하는 방탄소년단을 위해서 난 방탄소년단의 노래를 듣고 오래오래 덕질을 할 것이다. 솔직히 많은 사람들이 초심을 잃었다며 탈덕을 하고 있는데 오히려 그들이 초심을 잃은게 아닐까라는 생각을 조심스럽게해본다. 계속해서 우리를 위해 곡을 만들고 무리해서 스케쥴을 소화하고 이러한 스케쥴, 공연 속에서 음이탈이 한번이라도 발생하면 헤이터들에게 비난을 받음에도 우리들을 위해 음악을 하고 있는 방탄소년단의 초심이 변했다는 것이 나는 이해가 가지 않는다. 탈덕을 하던 헤이터들이 욕을 하던 방탄소년단은 내 마음 속에서 빛나는 나의 영원한 아이돌이다. 나의 아티스트, 나의 우상, 나의 사랑 그리고 내 삶의 활력소이자 원동력인 방탄소년단이 항상 빛나는 아티스트가 되도록 할것이다. 넓은 공연장을 빛내는 아미 중 하나일 것이다.

author: @布川由紀子
text:
ナムさんが、ゲストの時にも
同じようなことを話していたよーな。BTSをずっと続けていきたい
❤❤❤😂と。
腰の曲がったおじいちゃんに
なったとしても、7人で寄り添っていっていたい😊

きっとアーミーは、
常に与えられた環境を全力で
頑張り続けるBTSを見て沢山の
力をもらっているし。

応援し続けていきたいなと
思わせてくれるんだろうな😂😂

ナムさんが泣きながら、
疲れたと言えなかった。もっと韓国のアイドルたちに、仕事を続けられる環境を与えてほしい😢
と話してくれてから、それぞれが
新しい環境を歩き出してから…

私は、まだアーミー1年目で
まだまだひよっこ🐣で、分からないことばかりだけど、
でも、メンバーが　程よく自然体の自分を見せてくれていたり、
尊敬するアーティストとのコラボを実現したり。BTSが諦めずに
続けてきたご褒美として、色々なことが、新しくより良い方向に向かって進んでいるように、思います。日本の46歳の遅咲きの
アーミーですが、いつまでBTSを見ていきたいです❤❤❤

author: @Jo-ld7zn
text:
Uno siembra y otro cosecha. Att, el Agust D.

Los amo y los admiro tanto. Verlos que han logrado llegar a un estado de tranquilidad con su carrera y sus vidas me hace sentirme feliz por ellos. Y sí, lo que venga, lo que quieran hacer y hagan con sus vidas, está bien, solo sean muy felices. Porque la felicidad de quienes nos inspiran también es nuestra felicidad.

Sin dudas los consejos de Yoongi son siempre tan acertados y siento que tiene las palabras correctas para cada etapa. Somos como compañeros de camino. Cuando dijo "¿Qué harás si no puedes? ¿Vas a llorar? No. Hazlo. Se lo digo a mi yo del futuro. Hazlo", se sintió como un consejo para mí en el momento preciso.

Te amo genio Min Yoongi, muchos éxitos en tu gira. Ya nos veremos en la gira mundial cuando estén todos de regreso.

author: @arlm9969
text:
감사합니다, 저희(아미)를 이해해주셔서 감사합니다. 디데이 투어 콘서트에 갈 수 없어서 너무 슬프고 콘서트에 갈 수 없지만 2017 년에 방탄소년단을 만난 것은 정말 행운이라고 생각합니다, 당신은 내 존재를 모르지만 내 삶을 향상시키기 위해 왔습니다, 당신은 나의 음악, 나의 기쁨, 나의 동기 부여, 영감, 내가 가장 좋아하는 사람들, 나의 우주, 당신을 너무 사랑합니다, 진실은 당신을 만나기 전에 어떻게 살았는지 전혀 모릅니다. 여러분 7명이 함께 있는 모습을 보면 제 삶에 활력이 생기고, 여러분은 제 일상의 행복이에요, 여러분 없이는 제가 어떻게 살아야 할지 모르겠어요, 정말 사랑해요 ❤
시간을 거슬러 올라가면 2013년부터 여러분을 만나 처음부터 응원하고 함께할 수 있었으면 좋았을 텐데, 이렇게 만나게 되어 감사하게 생각합니다. 내 인생에 존재해줘서 고마워 :")

당신을 사랑하는 아미💜

GRACIAS SUGA, gracias por entendernos (a ARMY). Estoy muy triste porque no voy a poder ir al concierto de D-DAY tour, tampoco he podido ir a ninguno de los conciertos, pero saben que, yo me siento muy afortunada de haber conocido a BTS en el 2017, ustedes no conocen mi existencia, pero llegaron a mejorar mi vida, ustedes son mi música, mi alegría, mi motivación, mi inspiración, mis personas favoritas y mi universo, los AMO tanto, la verdad no tengo idea de como vivía antes de conocerlos. text: Yo también pienso igual, a veces me da la sensación que no tiene el mismo apoyo de los demás compañeros, veo que los otros se apoyan más o por lo menos es más visible, no sabemos lo que hablan entre ellos, tal vez si hablan más con RM, pero veo mucha tristeza y resignación en la mirada de Nam y realmente él es increíble, su álbum Índigo es una obra de culto, no es música para cualquiera como puede ser la de los demás, es para gente más culta en género musical, tal vez por eso tiene menos apoyo su álbum por parte de Army. Además el dijo que no hizo el álbum para todo el mundo ni para que tuviera mucho apoyo sino para que perdurara en el tiempo. Creo que el tiempo que esté en el servicio militar le va a venir bien para desconectar completamente, conocer gente nueva, etc. A los demás nos queda esperar a 2025 para ver que pasa y seguir apoyando a todos.

author: @lafammemalkavian
text: Muchas gracias chicos, de verdad que mientras más los escucho más los quiero, de verdad que sí nos ayudan a transitar nuestras propias vidas de mejor manera, más reflexiva, nos inspiran y nos dan un ejemplo de resiliencia e inteligencia emocional, verlos crecer nos ayuda mucho a mirar nuestra propia vida en perspectiva, aún a ARMYS adultas como yo, a mis 42 años transitando otros procesos y otras etapas de la vida, en otro contexto completamente diferente, me dan buenas lecciones que me ayudan a aterrizar mis proyectos por qué estoy viendo un poco de lo que hacen ustedes para lograrlo, lo que nos comparten es muy muy importante, me ayudan a cambiar la perspectiva  que yo tengo muchas veces de mi realidad. Yo estoy en plena reconstrucción de mi vida después de una relación de 17 años y recién ahora estoy mejor luego de muchas crisis horribles que pase desde pequeña y está última, voy saliendo de otra depresión mayor y ataques de pánico y ansiedad, estoy creando un nuevo proyecto que si es mi verdadera vocación y de verdad en el proceso que estoy haciendo, aprendiendo y actualizandome, constantemente me acuerdo de ustedes, de sus letras y sus anécdotas de vida, tengo muchos referentes que me inspiran desde mi juventud, pero en este momento de mi vida es justo su mensaje el que necesito para inspirarme, darme ánimos y creer en mi, yo decidí no tener hijos y soy fan de metal y rock, soy más bien gótica, pero de alguna manera  un día los descubrí escuché su mensaje, conocí su historia y  me abrieron la mente a nueva música y a romper mis prejuicios rancios respecto al  mundo del "pop" , ustedes demuestran lo que es ser un músico y un artista completo, y ver su proceso para llegar a ser quienes son, es muy motivador, cada que dudo y decaigo, los recuerdo, su ética, perseverancia, duciplina, su capacidad de reflexión, su resiliencia, su humanidad, y eso me ayuda a creer en mi también, gracias chicos. Un abrazo desde Ciudad de México

author: @poeticfilmssociety
text:
"Every Moment is a choice."

"The people who pave the way feel rewarded even though it's hard."

"But in the end creating intangible content is like a punishment. It is something we just have to bear."

"Time that never comes back feels more beautiful."

"My dream is to live in present.
For example during Joseon's dynasty, they'd sleep when the Sun went down. They were just living in the present in a way. These days people are so focused on the past or future and it is really easy to do that but both the past and future are created by the present, so If I can live my life while focusing on my current state and feelings then no matter what choices I make, I don't think I will regret them.
So, my dream is to live in the present. Isn't it funny though? Because dreams are for the future..."

©RM

author: @BM-ur4je
text:
This was a particularly meaningful experience. Both RM and Yoongi spoke from the heart releasing so many unspoken thoughts and feelings accumulated and experienced over the 10+ years of being BTS. It is deep and shows a personality of each of them...Yoongi in particular (since he's the subject of the gathering) - that could not be gleaned no matter how many videos of them over the years you watched. It brought tears to my eyes as parts resonated with my own life experiences. Both appear not to have been negatively affected by fame and fortune. Rather the opportunities opened up to them finally are being slowly realized. It was especially heartwarming to hear Suga's desire for the 7 of them to always stay more than friends no matter what the future brings to each individually. This is a truly rare deep view into a young Korean man's passage through life with such beautiful outcomes as these two represent.
Y

author: @suzyzoo5545
text: Well spoken RM, its is hard to live in the present, working, eating and doing things do not amount to just living in the present. Living in the present is to embrace hearing, feeling, thinking in the present cos most of the time we don't give people our 100% attention, or ourselves 100% attention. Our tots or attnetion can be what happened yesterday or in the past or what is going to happen tomorrow or in the future. To be present 100% in the moment is hard. When you are young, you think of the future more, when you are older you think about the past and future more, and when you are really old you think about the past more. Its the way of life. Because when you are older, you have lived thru yr life and then you realise somehow you are just going to get more of the same same.

author: @Blueof...
text:
Me encantan ambos ahora también quiero un programa de RM en el cual nos indique sobre sus obras y tremendas conversaciones profundas que ambos se manejan. waaa es tan genial sentirse orgullosa de las personas que sigues las personas que llevas de ejemplo de vida.
Fuera de la presión que a veces por seguirlos podemos generar sobre ellos, es mas agradable verlos disfrutando el momento de sus vidas, fuera de todo siempre he seguido a BTS porque no solo logran transmitir su sacrificio, sus risas y fu esfuerzo.  Sino son como un libro abierto, siento esa calidez al   seguirlos es como a un familiar, los siento tan cercanos que verlos felices en actividades diarias o en su día a día me hace muy feliz.
Fuera de todo se que debo enfocarme en mi y al verlo me dan tantas ganas de llevar una vida en paz y poder seguir escuchando su arte, no me confundan no vivo 100% pegada a las cosas que ellos hacen, tengo mi carrera y mis hobbies tengo 25 años y me siento en calma gracias a muchas de sus palabras compartidas a través de sus canciones, es genial poder sentir esa tranquilidad que ellos generan, yo se que ellos tienen vidas personales pero no saben las veces que agradezco que ellos hayan elegido su carrera, hayan elegido transmitir y expresar sus emociones por estos medios. 

Por eso creo que al igual que todas mis hermanas el protegerlos es una de nuestras principales prioridades, cuando los artistas salen transmiten tanto que ya sea que generan popularidad también en algunos les generan odio, y lo mejor que una fan puede hacer es defender sin sobrepasar nuestro limite. Y chicas yo por esas estrellas seguiré viviendo tranquila, feliz y defendiéndolos, me siento feliz de verlos brillar,  se que todos los caminos son difíciles pero ellos, estas bellas 7 estrellas decidieron brillar como ninguna y yo protegeré ese brillo.

author: @alexgraffigne7526
text:
The love they have for each other is just so big 🥹 they're not the type to show it much, but you can clearly see it in these moments.
Like how episode 1 of suchwita was Namjoon, and when Yoongi needed an replacement mc to promote his own stuff, he chose Namjoon again.
Like how they can't help but always mention how many years they've been friends.
Like how the time Yoongi wants to go back to is when they only had each other, no group, no fame, no recognition.
Like how even though Yoongi said he didn't want to talk about the past today, they talked about it for half the episode.
Like how they both worry about each other, but don't say anything, just look from the outside and watch each other grow.
Like how Namjoon can call Yoongi cute and an embarrassment in the span of 2 minutes, and Yoongi won't react to either of those because they just know.
Like the quiet bickering all throughout the episode.
Like how Namjoon calls him hyungie most of the time, and Yoongi always mentions how he's their leader and the best at it.

I could go on but I'm crying too much I need a friendship like that in my life

author: @화평-y2n
text:
저는 아미는 아니지만 agust d 의 곡이 나올때마다 너무 놀라고 위로받고 시원해요.
세상에 대한 날카로운 통찰과 따뜻한 시선이 동시에 담겨있으면서 한국적인 요소를 버무려낸 슈가의 음악이 참 좋습니다.
특히 이번 앨범에서 극야라는 곡은 무한반복하고 있어요.
우리나라 아티스트 중에 가장 경이로운 음악적 업적을 달성하는데 언론에서는 그만큼 노출이 안되죠. 그리고 언론에서 방탄의 업적만큼 평가받지 못하고 있는 것 같아요. 물론 그들의 평가는 중요하지 않지만요.
정상의 자리에서 황색언론들을 향해 할 말을 하는 음악을 만들어줘서 감사해요.
앞으로 오랫동안 행복하게 음악을 해 주세요.
아미는 아니지만 방탄의 음악에 때때로 위로 받는 사람인데 주절주절 남겨봅니다.

author: @marielbonilla454
text: Me encantó este Episodio, se encontraron dos talentos y hablaron un mismo idioma, sobre crear música!!! Fue muy lindo escuchar todo lo que contó Yoongi sobre todo el proceso que tuvo la creación de su último Álbum!!! Debe de ser cierto que no puede vivir sin estar escribiendo su música, ya que nació para eso, su necesidad de hacerlo es lo mismo que respirar !!! Por lo visto su naturaleza inquieta, ha hecho que tenga muchas ganas de producir, cantar y actuar y por lo que se ha visto, todo lo hace de manera excelente, es un hombre muy talentoso y audaz, ya que se atreve a realizar una Gira Internacional en solitario, eso no es para cualquiera!!! La charla me pareció muy entretenida y amena, se notó la confianza, el cariño y sobre todo el respeto y la admiración mutua , fueron muy simpáticas esas bromas que se dijeron y la imagen del cierre del programa me resultó muy  tierna!!! Yoongi, ha sufrido un gran cambio y con éste trabajo, como él mismo lo dijo, está dejando atrás su pasado y todos los malos recuerdos que le quedaron sobre esa etapa tan difícil de su vida y que le producía tanto enojo y rebeldía, está haciendo un "borrón y cuenta nueva", se lo nota como más relajado y seguro de sí mismo, más alegre y extrovertido, lo más seguro es que siempre haya sido asi, pero recién ahora, nos deja ver esa faceta de su personalidad y a mí en lo personal, me fascina!!! Acá no se termina su trabajo, es un creador incansable, por lo que pienso que sus próximos trabajos como Suga, serán muy diferentes a éste último trabajo, eso nos va a permitir seguir disfrutando y conociendo a nuestro amado Yoongi!!! Estoy segura que su gira va a ser todo un éxito!!! 😍🐨🥰🥰🥰❤️❤️❤️

author: @mbrr8616
text:
People usually ask what the formula for BTS’ success is and it seems nowadays they have become the “template” the industry follows. The truth is, I think more than anything, the marketing, the “packaging”, they’ve somehow shown us their SINCERITY and their IMMENSE TALENT and have shown how AUTHENTIC they are. The message in their music, their affection for each other and how much they care for the Armys. One can see that it’s NOT CONTRIVED and I truly appreciate and love that of BTS. Thank you for existing in my lifetime and thank you for your music and adding color and happiness in my life. More power to you 💜💜💜

PS: D DAY and HAEGEUM ROCKS 🤟🏻

author: @ashleyashley12345
text:
First, this was adorable. Second, the conversation about living in the present was very thought-provoking for me. I am dealing with some things in my own life, and I worry about the future too much. I need to focus on the present and go from there.

I am happy to hear that Yoongi is feeling less pessimistic these days, and that RM is feeling more relaxed. I am still baby ARMY myself, but I have noticed in videos of them in the past that they did seem stressed. I hope that they continue to grow more and more relaxed and positive as the days pass.

Thank you both for another great interview. It was fun to see the show come full circle from the first episode with this one. 💜

author: @dorysrodriguezpinchi6656
text: Este episodio suchwita ha sido muy interesante estaban dos grandes de la música, nuestro querido líder entrevistando a Agust D. SUGA trabajo mucho para este álbum como productor, escritor, contando muchas historias de su vida tratando decir lo que siente sin importar lo que puedan decir como el mismo  dijo sin filtros, eso me encanta, se veía nuestro líder muy emocionado que  cada uno brilla por luz propia y  que cada álbum o alguna otra actividad que hagan siempre piensan en ARMY.  Me emocione que SUGA dijera que sueño es que en el futuro esten los 7  por mucho tiempo hasta que sean abuelo por que son como una familia. Apoyemos siempre a estos maravillosos chicos por que son muy valioso y vale pena, son ejemplos a seguir que avpesar de la diferencia de edad que tengan  han sabido manejar dificultades en la vida y eso es algo valorable. Mi Suga hermoso tengas todo el éxito en tu gira mundial, espero algún día conocerlos a todos ustedes no pierdo las esperanza que se día llegara.

text: Мне 69 лет, два года назад потеряла близкого , любимого человека. author: @rani-nam
text:
오늘 수취타를 보면서 남준이랑 슈가의 대화중에 "아미가 우리 노래로 살아갈 힘을 얻고 우리도 그런 아미에게 힘을 얻는다"라는 대목에서 내가 처음 우리 방탄이를 알게 되고 덕질이란걸 하게 된 과거가 불연듯 스치더라.
32평 아파트에서 겜방 옷방 두고 내인생의 주인공으로 살다가 단 몇년만에 단칸 원룸 나락으로 떨어지고 내인생에서조차 행인123 처럼 엑스트라가 되어버린거 같은때. 방구석에 쳐박혀서 핸폰이나 끄적거리고 ㅈㅅ이나 검색하던 시절... 유튭 추천 알고리즘은 그때나 지금이나 신기한게 삶에 희망을 주는 내용의 영상만 그렇게 추천이 뜨더라 아마도 저 단어를 몇번 검색한게 원인이었던거 같아.ㅎㅎ 그중에 어느 팬이 올려놓은 소우주의 가사 포함한 영상을 보게 됐는데 침대에 반 누워서 그거 보다가 갑자기 울컥했었네... 드라마나 영화보면서도 한번도 울어본적없는 공감능력없는 내가 눈물이 주루룩 나더라. 가사를 보면서 노래를 듣는데 마치 나한테 위로랍시고 해주는 말같은거야.. 깊은밤에 더 빛나는 별빛 70억개의 빛으로 빛나는 70억개의 월드 넌 누구보다도 밝게빛나. 이런 가사들이 가슴에 와서 큐피트의 화살처럼 팍팍 꼿히더라.
그때까지도 난 BTS가 누군지 몰랐어. 바로 검색을 해보니 "아 봄날!! 이노랜 알지" 이정도였거든... 그후에 BTS검색해서 나오는 영상들 보다보니 입덕하게 됐고 노래를 찾아듣다보니 가사들이 당시의 나에게 위로해주는 내용들이 많았고 그렇게 내가 ㅈㅅ 이라는 걸 하지않고 그 생각을 잊고 그 시간을 지나오게 됐더라구. 진짜 하루종일 방탄이들 영상 보면서 웃고 울다가 잠들고 이걸 거의 반년을 했네. 완전 은둔형외톨이의 생활이었지만 나름 나에겐 버티는 시간이었고 그걸 같이 버텨주고 옆에서 힘이 되준건 방탄이들이었지. 본인들은 모르겠지만 ㅎㅎ 그래서 내가 탈덕을 못해. 난 그냥 아미고 이대로 평생 갈거 같아. 그냥 내가 숨쉬는게 당연하듯 아미인게 당연한... 뭐 그런거??  나이를 보면 아마도 내가 아미인체로 죽는게 더 빠를거 같으니까 우리 BTS는 나에겐 영원한 우상이 되겠지. 내가 죽기전엔 해체하거나 맴버가 빠지거나 하는 변화는 없었으면 좋겠어 ㅜㅜ 내가 우리 방탄이들에게 바라는건 그거 하나뿐이다.

text: I related with it so much, Yoongi talking about having Agust D as a place to share things that were a little heavy, dark, that consumed him in a way that it affected his mental space. I have always felt things intensely and they consume me to a point that if I don't write it down, I will combust. And I have always had a hard time with sharing those parts of me that are angry and hurt and a little dark, that are hopeless and raging and that is why I did start a separate place to put down those thoughts. Both are me, parts of me, but one carries a lot of burden of the world and that can feel heavy sometimes sharing it with someone else as you are can feel really scary and burdensome.

author: @dianaanngallardo2230
text:
I think one of BTS' appeals is the way they humanize idols/singers. They have their dark moments, and they won't paint them with rainbows just to avoid making some people uncomfortable. Sure, they don't really darken the whole room either, but they let others have, at the very least, a glimpse of how it is like for them to be humans too. And that, I think, is a big part of their almost-unbreakable connection with their fans. ❤

And this conversation between RM and Suga just cemented that some more. 😊

author: @proudArmy
text:
I'm in awe, guys! 💜💜It's hard to articulate what I'm thinking. K-pop to me was a cohesive, formless mass until I found BTS. All performers are the same, twelve are a dozen.

But they stood out from the other bands. 💜💜
They touched on something that is common to all of us humans, and that is the struggle with our own darkness, traumas, and demons. At the same time, they also offered light, comfort and strength through their songs.
The most outstanding example of this is Yoongi and Jiminie. Both are huge, groundbreaking artists.
Yoongi has created a rap style never before heard that is inimitable and unique to him. 🔥🔥
Jiminie has created a never-before-seen dance style that is unique to him and also inimitable. And also, his voice... Whenever Jiminie sings, his voice seems masculine, feminine, harsh, and gentle at the same time, depending on what he wants to convey. HE CAN TRANSMIT EVERYTHING, because such a voice is born once every 100 years, but maybe not even then.

I've been in shock since yesterday, when I listened to Yoongi's album for the first time, and now again when I saw Amygdala's MV for the first time this afternoon. I am in awe of how he is able to so intelligently, sophisticatedly and objectively, and at such a high artistic level, put into shape all this pain that he has kept inside himself. 😥😥😥😥
He is so mature and wise, as if he is not 30, but 3000 years old and has poured the pain and experience of every life he has lived into this album. This has to be digested, it is pure, raw art.

This is not k-pop anymore, this is really the beginning of Yoongi's legend.
I wouldn't be surprised if, in 10 years, the dance and rap style created by the two of them would be considered a new independent genre. 💜💜They deserve to become immortal and to have their work become teaching material in music and dance schools. 💜💜

author: @pranathisridhar969
text:
I've been ARMY for almost 6years now and I don't know how time flew.
Crucial reason why I am ARMY is because BTS taught and is teaching me how to deal with life. I've been a topper throughout my life but, I've never been able to learn how to live. BTS taught me how to live. How to enjoy life, how to deal with failure, how to cope up with your emotions and most importantly how to love yourself no matter how you are and who you are in the moment. I think I needed someone in that moment in life to help me love myself and BTS was and will always be there for me.
I love BTS because I love the way the team is, their ideals, principles and thoughts they motivate me like no other thing.
Apobangpo💜
2025 here we come.......

text: Да, БТС появились в моей жизни когда я была в тупике. Осознание того от того что живёшь не своей жизнью и нет близких людей с которыми можно было об этом поговорить вгоняло в депрессивное состояние. Но моё мышление изменилось с одного короткого ролика. Это был фрагмент "For youth " , так погружаясь в музыку, жизнь и контент мемберов осознала, что начала двигаться (хоть и маленькими шагами) вперёд. У меня нет возможности благодарить мемберов материально из-за санкций наложенных на Россию, но я могу нести их мессендж людям. Вот так зажигая огоньки в людях, мы можем изменить мир к лучшему 😊

text:
Meu Deus, que episódio foi esse?
Eu to eufórica aqui. RM e Suga juntos, com essa vibe tao descontraida.
Amei ver o SUGA assim felizinho e surpreendido pela noticia sobre sua conquista no Spotify. Ele ainda nao se conscientizou do Rei que é.
Também foi muito agradável ver o Nam sendo o MC do programa. Ele é muito bom em tudo que se propõe a fazer, nao é mesmo?
Tambem nao posso deixar passar batido a parte em que ele menciona o JK e a Ck. È obvio que estamos adorando essa fase do BTS, porém, 7 é melhor que 1. Nunca conseguiremos superar a emoçao e a alegria que sao os 7 juntos. 
Eu gostei muito de todos os episodios de SUCHWITA. Mas esse sem dúvida, é o meu favorito. Estou no auge com esse episodio.

author: @campusvixen
text:
I bet myself I wouldn’t shed a tear this episode, but I couldn’t help it knowing that they feel as lucky they can live through army the same way we feel lucky to live through their meaningful music/stories/messages/convictions. 

I’ve always worried they’d feel the most pressured by all the deserved love they receive, but despite all pressures I’m so thankful they didn’t sacrifice their music/art/personality to be compromised. Otherwise, I wouldn’t love them so much as I do. 

With how things are, I trust my boys make wise decisions; even when things are hard, they’ll suppress it with their own hardwork. Only BTS is able to do their work in that sense without compromising so much.

Stay healthy, everyone in this family 💜

author: @undomiel972
text:
Oh these two 🥹🫶🏻 i am really loving all these bangtan contents rn. There was taekook attending the vip premiere looking cute together and now this Namgi talking about life and music. Yoongi is really soft these days. As he enters a new chapter in his life, im glad thats he’s in a better place mentally and glad thats he’s able to talk about it. Im really also proud of him for overcoming. Bangtan 2.0 is really even better. Im glad that theyre more relaxed esp Namjoon, free from society’s expectations and just living in the present. They dont need to do much these days because their hardwork paid off and the results show. Its such a joy to watch them talking and reminiscing and being just so grounded even after all their success. Theyre such genuine souls. 💜💜 

D-day is really something, snooze is my favorite so far and that life goes on in yoongis verse is chefs kiss. Its such a healing album. Just like how Indigo is. BTS, hwaiting! Well always support you guys in whatever you do in the present and in the future. Borahae 🫶🏻🫶🏻

author: @schafferable
text: SNOOZE is the most encouraging song, and although I can glean from/or interpret what I need from the lyrics it really is a word for other Korean artists and anyone who is trying to be successful in work and life itself. Suga/AgustD is saying "Hey, I'm here, I know how you feel, I've struggled with the lie of fear, darkness, and hopelessness - don't give in to the lie that life isn't worth living, let's talk first before doing anything to hurt yourself, your family, your friends, or the ones who love you... everything's gonna be alright... don't do anything without talking to me first or seeking out help; I know the way; I care about you; I'll help you succeed; I'll give you advice". (" " my interpretation loosely) I love the openness of this song - it is full of love and compassion, and very thoughtful. Who doesn't need compassion? In light of what happened last week to our dear Moonbin, I believe the message never gets old. I hope BTS repeats the Love Yourself message because they have a loving platform. Just because it has been done once doesn't mean it can't be addressed again, especially by those who have found a way to make it through a dark moment. Shadows will repeatedly raise their ugly heads, and what we have learned before can help us survive easier in the next. So Suga, RM, and BTS, please keep addressing these issues... they never get old or go away we all need Hope.

author: @aralinya2652
text:
As always, Bangtan with Bangtan is the best. So much to love here - and guys, we've all known it for years, but Namjoon's making it official: Jimin wears clothes only to take them off and grows his hair out just so he can shake it. 😂

What I really don't love is the PPL. Why is it that in all the years before Big Hit became HYBE there were never any ads in BTS content, and now that the company's become this massive money making machine they've suddenly started putting ads in everywhere? It's not like they need the extra cash. I mean, it's kind of funny seeing the members switch into acting mode, but I hate how fake it all is. Surely it's not just me who feels this way?

author: @claire-joy
text:
이제 방탄에 대한 내 마음을
어떤 말과 글로 표현해야 할지 모르겠다.
탄이들을 보고 있으면
유쾌하게 웃다가도 미안해지고,
뿌듯하고 자랑스러우면서도 애닲고,
대견하다가도 존경스럽다.
어떤 모습으로든, 어디서 무엇을 하든
그저 고맙고, 다행이고, 응원해주게 된다.
본인의 결정과 본인의 속도에 맞춰 
어떻게든 자신의 삶과 방탄의 삶을 
균형 있게 잘 살아내고야 말 친구들인 걸 
너무 잘 알기에,
열렬한 응원과 무조건적인 지지가 아니더라도
그저 들꽃을 바라보듯 
미소 띤 얼굴로 
가만가만 지켜봐 주고 싶은 마음.
나 하나가 탄이들을 위해 
뭐 얼마나 큰 응원과 지지를 해줄 수 있겠냐마는 
내 일상의 순간순간, 그리고 마음으로
멀리서나마 탄이들을 늘 응원하고 아낀다는 걸,
그리고 그 마음은 몸과 함께 나이 들어가겠지만
변하지는 않을 거란 걸, 
이제는 나도 알 것 같다.
늦게나마 탄이들을 알게 되어 
문득 고마운 밤.💜

author: @imac_328
text: Thank you so much for this Guys. 💖I really loved Episode 9 with Guest Host, RM, and Special Guest, Artist Agust D/Suga and creatively inspirational, yet down to earth being, Min Yoon-gi. The conversation flowed easily and freely, it was a fun and casual atmosphere, and the open ended questions, utilized by both, allowed ARMY the ability to learn more about the inner depth that resides within both of these men. I especially enjoyed hearing about Yoon-gi getting away from the City to a place of solace when he needed it. Natural peacefulness in order to effectively gain the rest, relaxation, and inner calm necessary to productively and effectively write and compose D Day's music. I'll most certainly listen to the entire Album's music and lyrics with deep respect and appreciation for the humble genius of a man who created it. Thank you for sharing, BangtanTV, and have a wonderful day. 💜 Irene

text: Happiness overload...Love this R-chwita episode with AgustD...So fun and refreshing to watch...Namjoon did great in this episode...Yoongi and Joon is so cute and adorable...2 brothers comfortably talking about life and music...Nothing to ask for...Love their genuine friendship...So happy that we get to know more about AgustD...Always have a huge admiration to him as an artist...His music is so comforting and heartwarming...Love the honesty and sincere emotions in his songs...D-Day is a masterpiece album...Can't wait for the exciting things that AgustD will do...From the album to the documentary and the tour...It is going to be so much fun...He is really spoiling ARMYs...Felt the genuine love and care for the members and the fandom...Enjoy the tour with ARMYs AgustD...And got teary eyed when they were talking about Bangtan...Wishing for more precious moments with our forever 7...This is just a short pause and we'll get to see them together again...Can't wait for that moment to come....Let's continue to support them on their solo projects...And wait patiently for them...Fighting Yoongi...Fighting Bangtan...Thank you Namjoon for an amazing interview with AgustD...APOBANGPO...Until We meet Again....Borahae💜
